Definition: charge falsely or with malicious intent
Example: attack the good name and reputation of someone; The journalists have defamed me!; The article in the paper sullied my reputation
Synonyms: adj, all, harmful, defamatory, noun, communication, defamation, act, person, defamer, slander, slanderer, smirch, asperse, aspersion, denigrate, denigratory, denigration, calumniate, calumny, smear, sully, besmirch, charge, falsely, or, with, malicious, intent, attack, the, good, name, and, reputation, of, someone, The, journalists, have, defamed, me, article, in, paper, sullied, my
Frame: 9,10
Category: verb.communication
